---
import PolicyLayout from '../layouts/PolicyLayout.astro';
---

<PolicyLayout title="Cookie Policy" lastUpdated="30/10/2025">

  <section class="mb-8">
    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-brand-dark mb-3">1. What Are Cookies</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
      Cookies are small text files that are placed on your computer or mobile device when you visit a website. They are widely used to make websites work more efficiently, as well as to provide information to the owners of the site. Cookies allow a website to recognise your device and remember certain information about your visits, such as your preferences and browsing history.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-8">
    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-brand-dark mb-3">2. How We Use Cookies</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
      Keane International Legal Consultancy LLP ("KILC") uses cookies on our website (<a href="https://kilc.co.uk" class="text-brand-accent hover:underline">kilc.co.uk</a>) to improve your browsing experience, analyse website traffic, and understand how visitors interact with our site. We use cookies in accordance with applicable data protection laws, including the UK GDPR and the Privacy and Electronic Communications Regulations 2003 (PECR).
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-8">
    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-brand-dark mb-3">3. Types of Cookies We Use</h3>

    <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-brand-dark mb-2 mt-4">Essential Cookies</h4>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
      These cookies are strictly necessary for the operation of our website. They enable core functionality such as page navigation, access to secure areas, and language preferences. The website cannot function properly without these cookies, and they cannot be switched off in our systems.
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-4">
      <li><strong>Language preference:</strong> Remembers your chosen language (English or Chinese) so you do not need to select it on every visit.</li>
      <li><strong>Session management:</strong> Maintains your session state as you navigate between pages.</li>
      <li><strong>Cookie consent:</strong> Records whether you have accepted or declined non-essential cookies.</li>
    </ul>

    <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-brand-dark mb-2 mt-4">Analytics Cookies</h4>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
      These cookies help us understand how visitors interact with our website by collecting and reporting information anonymously. We use self-hosted analytics (not Google Analytics) to ensure your data stays on our own servers and is not shared with third parties.
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-4">
      <li><strong>Page views:</strong> Tracks which pages are visited to help us understand which content is most useful.</li>
      <li><strong>Referral source:</strong> Identifies how visitors arrived at our website (e.g., search engine, direct visit, or link from another site).</li>
      <li><strong>Device and browser information:</strong> Collects general technical information to help us optimise the website for different devices.</li>
    </ul>

    <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-brand-dark mb-2 mt-4">Functionality Cookies</h4>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
      These cookies allow the website to remember choices you make and provide enhanced, more personalised features. They may be set by us or by third-party providers whose services we have added to our pages.
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-4">
      <li><strong>Theme preference:</strong> Remembers your preferred display settings (e.g., light or dark mode).</li>
      <li><strong>Form data:</strong> May temporarily store information you have entered into forms to prevent data loss.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-8">
    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-brand-dark mb-3">4. Third-Party Cookies</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
      We do not use any third-party advertising or tracking cookies. Our analytics are self-hosted, and we do not share your browsing data with external advertising platforms. Any third-party services integrated into our website (such as Cloudflare for security) may set their own cookies, which are governed by their respective privacy policies.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-8">
    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-brand-dark mb-3">5. Managing Your Cookie Preferences</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
      You can control and manage cookies in several ways:
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-4">
      <li><strong>Browser settings:</strong> Most web browsers allow you to control cookies through their settings. You can set your browser to refuse cookies, delete existing cookies, or alert you when a cookie is being set. Please note that disabling cookies may affect the functionality of our website.</li>
      <li><strong>Cookie consent:</strong> When you first visit our website, you will be presented with a cookie banner that allows you to accept or decline non-essential cookies.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
      For more information about how to manage cookies in your specific browser, please visit your browser's help pages:
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-4">
      <li><a href="https://support.google.com/chrome/answer/95647" class="text-brand-accent hover:underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Chrome</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://support.mozilla.org/en-US/kb/cookies-information-websites-store-on-your-computer" class="text-brand-accent hover:underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Mozilla Firefox</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://support.apple.com/en-gb/guide/safari/sfri11471/mac" class="text-brand-accent hover:underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Apple Safari</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/microsoft-edge/manage-cookies-in-microsoft-edge-view-allow-block-delete-and-use-168dab11-0753-043d-7c16-ede5947fc64d" class="text-brand-accent hover:underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Microsoft Edge</a></li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-8">
    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-brand-dark mb-3">6. Changes to This Cookie Policy</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
      We may update this cookie policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices or for operational, legal, or regulatory reasons. Any changes will be posted on this page with an updated revision date.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-8">
    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-brand-dark mb-3">7. Contact Us</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
      If you have any questions about our use of cookies, please contact us:
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-4">
      <li><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:privacy@kilc.co.uk" class="text-brand-accent hover:underline">privacy@kilc.co.uk</a></li>
      <li><strong>Post:</strong> Keane International Legal Consultancy LLP, 128 City Road, London EC1V 2NX</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
      For more information about your data protection rights, please refer to our <a href="/privacy-policy" class="text-brand-accent hover:underline">Privacy Policy</a>.
    </p>
  </section>

</PolicyLayout>
